                <h2>Why Reconciliation Keeps Failing</h2>
<p>When managing overseas ad spend, finance and ops teams typically face three pain points:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>充值 (Top-up)</strong>: Multiple platforms and accounts with different arrival times, causing balance discrepancies</li>
<li><strong>消耗 (Spend)</strong>: Platform-reported spend often doesn't match internal financial records due to timezone or attribution differences</li>
<li><strong>发票 (Invoices)</strong>: Long invoice issuance cycles create gaps between actual spend and documented amounts</li>
</ul>
<p>This checklist breaks down reconciliation into actionable steps across all three areas.</p>
<hr />
<h2>充值 (Top-up) Verification Checklist</h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Goal</strong>: Confirm every top-up is correctly recorded and matches platform balances.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Step 1: Compile Top-up Records</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Export all top-up transactions from payment channels (date, amount, account)</li>
<li>[ ] Cross-check against internal financial records (bank/credit card statements)</li>
<li>[ ] Tag each top-up with platform, account ID, and transaction reference</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 2: Verify Platform Arrival</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Log in to each ad platform and confirm received amounts</li>
<li>[ ] Watch for timezone issues—some platforms record in UTC</li>
<li>[ ] Flag any missing or partial arrivals</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 3: Handle Discrepancies</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] For missing top-ups: preserve proof and contact platform support</li>
<li>[ ] Log currency fluctuation differences separately</li>
<li>[ ] Open support tickets for long-pending top-ups</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>消耗 (Spend) Reconciliation Checklist</h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Goal</strong>: Ensure platform-reported spend matches financial records.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Step 4: Pull Platform Spend Reports</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Export spend reports from Meta Ads Manager, Google Ads, etc.</li>
<li>[ ] Align report date range with your billing cycle (calendar month or campaign week)</li>
<li>[ ] Record campaign-level spend for granular attribution</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 5: Compare Against Financial Records</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Total spend should match within ±2% tolerance</li>
<li>[ ] Larger gaps? Check attribution window settings (click vs. conversion)</li>
<li>[ ] Verify refunds are properly deducted from spend</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 6: Currency &amp; Exchange Rate Verification</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Confirm the exchange rate used (top-up date vs. spend date)</li>
<li>[ ] Ensure consistent currency conversion across all records</li>
<li>[ ] Log conversion differences as adjustment entries</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>发票 (Invoice) Matching Checklist</h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Goal</strong>: Align invoice amounts with actual spend for clean audits.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Step 7: Pre-Invoice Preparation</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Know each platform's invoice cycle (Meta issues monthly; Google may delay)</li>
<li>[ ] Verify company name and tax details are correct</li>
<li>[ ] Confirm which entity/contract each account belongs to</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 8: Invoice-to-Spend Matching</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Invoice amount should match net spend (消耗 minus refunds) for the billing period</li>
<li>[ ] Check if differences are due to taxes or coupon deductions</li>
<li>[ ] Archive invoices with corresponding spend reports</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 9: Filing &amp; Audit Trail</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Name invoice files by platform + month for easy retrieval</li>
<li>[ ] Tag invoice status in your financial system (received/posted/pending)</li>
<li>[ ] Set reminders to avoid missing invoices</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Common Discrepancy Quick Reference</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scenario</th>
<th>Likely Cause</th>
<th>Recommended Action</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Top-up deducted but not arrived</td>
<td>Payment channel delay</td>
<td>Wait 24h, then escalate</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Invoice &gt; Spend</td>
<td>Tax included, pre-paid balance</td>
<td>Review billing breakdown</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Invoice &lt; Spend</td>
<td>Partial invoice, pending refund</td>
<td>Wait for update or contact platform</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Spend vs. backend report mismatch</td>
<td>Attribution window, timezone, currency</td>
<td>Default to platform backend data</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>Recommended Reconciliation Frequency</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scenario</th>
<th>Frequency</th>
<th>When to Use</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Daily</td>
<td>Every day</td>
<td>High-spend accounts (&gt;$5000/day)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Weekly</td>
<td>Once a week</td>
<td>Mid-size teams running multiple campaigns</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Monthly</td>
<td>End of month</td>
<td>All overseas teams (required)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>Final Note</h2>
<p>The key to ad spend reconciliation is using <strong>platform data as the source of truth</strong> while cross-validating against your financial system. Complete monthly close reconciliation at the start of each month to leave buffer time for resolving discrepancies. If you need systematic reconciliation support or multi-account management, contact 以渔's operations team.</p>
